              The above three wordflow commands all belong to the
              same family, they may be intermixed as to the left side
              character, vs the right side character.  The last
              character to the right will determine the operation to be
              performed.
 
              The above three wordflow commands may be used in
              combination with the Zone command to "squeeze" text into a
              narrower column.
 
              EXAMPLE:  ??<<??z?????????????????????????z??<<?????????????
                        *  A big fat cow was eating all the    Text
                        *  green grass, while the sun was      outside of
                        *  shining.  So too were the birds.    the column
                        *                                      will not
                        *                                      be
                        *  But a lion was watching this cow.   altered
                        *                                      at all.
                                                                         ?
             yields:
                        *     A big fat cow was eating         Text
                        *     all the green grass, while       outside of
                        *     the sun was shining.  So         the column
                        *     too were the birds.              will not
                        *                                      be
                        *     But a lion was watching          altered
                        *     this cow.                        at all.
 
             Some comments on the "squeeze" operation.
             1)  If the text flows past the blank lines defining
                 paragraphs, then the text in the next paragraph will be
                 flowed together with the original text.  A WARNING
                 message will be issued to indicate that this has
                 occurred.  The text may come out as follows:
 
                        *         A big fat cow was            Text
                        *         eating all the green         outside of
                        *         grass, while the sun         the column
                        *         was shining.  So too         will not
                        *         were the birds.  But         be
                        *         a lion was watching          altered
                        *         this cow.                    at all.
 
                                                                         ?
             2)  If the text flows past the end of the defined column
                 depth, then an error message is issued, indicating the
                 start of the text that would be lost.  Text flow will
                 not be performed.
 
             3)  An unbalanced line command with one character
                 on the left and a double character on the right as in
                 ?????<?????????????????????????????????<<????????????
                 will put COL into a COLUMN PENDING mode but will still
                 execute the command and then redisplay the command.
                 This is useful when trying to progressively "squeeze"
                 or ("unsqueeze") text a step at a time.  Only the Z's
                 need to be re-entered.  Reset the command line when
                 finished.
 
             4)  If only one z is entered, it is assumed to be the left
                 zone and the right zone is assumed to be the right
                 textflow character.
